---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import portrait from "../assets/noah-airmet.jpg";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { site } from "../lib/site";
---

<BaseLayout>
  <section class="home-hero" aria-labelledby="home-title">
    <aside class="home-rail" aria-hidden="true">
      <span>Systems</span><span>Risk</span><span>Responsibility</span>
    </aside>

    <div class="hero-statement">
      <p class="indexed-label"><span>01</span> Working thesis</p>
      <h1 id="home-title">
        Build the system.<br />
        <em>Name the risk.</em><br />
        Make responsibility <strong>visible.</strong>
      </h1>
      <div class="hero-deck">
        <p>
          I’m a junior software developer and BYU cybersecurity student pursuing
          AI governance from the inside out: close to the code, the data, and the
          people who have to make controls work.
        </p>
        <a class="underlined-link" href="/work/">Explore selected work <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <aside class="hero-profile">
      <div>
        <p class="profile-kicker">A practical route into AI governance.</p>
        <p class="profile-fields">Software development · Security · Institutional controls</p>
      </div>
      <figure class="portrait-frame">
        <Image
          src={portrait}
          widths={[480, 720, 960]}
          sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 36vw"
          format="webp"
          alt="Noah Airmet smiling outdoors"
          loading="eager"
          fetchpriority="high"
        />
      </figure>
      <dl class="profile-facts">
        <div><dt>Now</dt><dd>Junior Developer, Simplicity Group</dd></div>
        <div><dt>Study</dt><dd>B.S. Cybersecurity, BYU · 2027</dd></div>
        <div><dt>Focus</dt><dd>AI governance + cybersecurity GRC</dd></div>
      </dl>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section class="operating-loop dark-section" aria-labelledby="loop-title">
    <div class="section-lead">
      <p class="indexed-label light"><span>02</span> The operating question</p>
      <h2 id="loop-title">Governance becomes real inside the workflow.</h2>
      <p>
        I’m interested in the point where broad principles become concrete
        decisions: what moves, who decides, what can fail, and what evidence
        survives.
      </p>
    </div>
    <ol class="loop-list">
      <li><span class="loop-number">01</span><strong>Build</strong><p>What does the system actually do?</p></li>
      <li><span class="loop-number">02</span><strong>Trace</strong><p>What data, authority, and dependencies move?</p></li>
      <li><span class="loop-number risk">03</span><strong>Challenge</strong><p>Where can it fail, mislead, or expose?</p></li>
      <li><span class="loop-number">04</span><strong>Govern</strong><p>What controls and evidence survive the workflow?</p></li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="selected-work content-section" aria-labelledby="work-title">
    <div class="section-heading-row">
      <div>
        <p class="indexed-label"><span>03</span> Selected work</p>
        <h2 id="work-title">Learning in public, building in practice.</h2>
      </div>
      <a class="underlined-link" href="/work/">All work <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></a>
    </div>

    <div class="work-feature-list">
      <article class="work-feature">
        <p class="work-index">01 / Active study</p>
        <div>
          <p class="work-kind">AI governance field guide</p>
          <h3><a href="/work/ai-grc-field-guide/">A dependency map from compute and capability to institutions and controls.</a></h3>
          <p>A theory-first program that turns each unit into a practical GRC artifact: assumption registers, control maps, stress tests, and decision memos.</p>
        </div>
        <a class="round-link" href="/work/ai-grc-field-guide/" aria-label="Read AI governance field guide case study">↗</a>
      </article>

      <article class="work-feature">
        <p class="work-index">02 / Systems research</p>
        <div>
          <p class="work-kind">Governing agent-operated systems</p>
          <h3><a href="/work/governing-agent-systems/">Making authority, evidence, and human intervention legible across AI agents.</a></h3>
          <p>Applied experiments in scoped capabilities, append-only records, review gates, escalation, and rollback for long-running agent work.</p>
        </div>
        <a class="round-link" href="/work/governing-agent-systems/" aria-label="Read governed agent systems case study">↗</a>
      </article>
    </div>

    <aside class="independent-project">
      <p class="work-kind">Independent work, kept distinct</p>
      <h3>Pulpit</h3>
      <p>
        An AI-assisted Latter-day Saint historical archive using OCR, source-linked
        transcription, provenance metadata, and tiered human review. Its full
        religious and operational story lives on its own site; I reference it
        here only where the archival method teaches something transferable.
      </p>
      <a href="https://pulpit.noahairmet.com">Visit Pulpit <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section class="principles content-section" aria-labelledby="principles-title">
    <div class="section-heading-row">
      <div>
        <p class="indexed-label"><span>04</span> Operating principles</p>
        <h2 id="principles-title">Controls should clarify responsibility—not decorate it.</h2>
      </div>
    </div>
    <ol class="principle-grid">
      <li><span>01</span><h3>Protect people and entrusted data.</h3><p>Security, privacy, and human dignity are the purpose of the control—not paperwork around it.</p></li>
      <li><span>02</span><h3>Keep responsibility legible.</h3><p>AI can assist the work. It cannot absorb accountability for the choices people make with it.</p></li>
      <li><span>03</span><h3>Build for the real workflow.</h3><p>A policy succeeds only when the people under pressure can understand, follow, and verify it.</p></li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="contact-section" aria-labelledby="contact-title">
    <p class="indexed-label light"><span>05</span> Start a conversation</p>
    <h2 id="contact-title">I’m looking for the next place to learn, build, and make AI accountability concrete.</h2>
    <div>
      <p>Open to 2027 roles, internships, research collaborations, and conversations about practical AI governance.</p>
      <a class="contact-button" href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>Email Noah <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
